<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-E516226F-EB8D-41AF-8C54-AEB31F919C9F" version="1" lang="en-US"?><concept xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-E516226F-EB8D-41AF-8C54-AEB31F919C9F" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic concept)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c concept oceConcept-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic concept/concept "><title class="- topic/title ">03 The function of the Z Motion System</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-34C6A3E5-E809-4139-80CC-275A8CCF9EDC"><p class="- topic/p ">The Z motion system provides a mechanism to ensure the correct distance between the printhead(s) and the media on the platen (print surface). 
</p><fig class="- topic/fig " id="GUID-6BFA373B-0704-46F6-BA4D-FD0C68280593"><title class="- topic/title ">Location of the Z motion system in yellow</title><image class="- topic/image " href="GUID-A8D3C35B-BB4B-49BC-A08E-93D7B0D946DE-low.png" placement="inline" otherprops="GUID-A8D3C35B-BB4B-49BC-A08E-93D7B0D946DE-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">Depending on the media type and weight the thickness of the media varies. The Z motion system positions the printhead(s) at the correct distance above the media. The complete printhead guidance system (Guide rail, printhead carriage with the 8 printheads and maintenance unit ) is lifted or lowered to achieve this. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The optimal distance between printhead(s) and media is approximately 1.675 mm. The maximal media thickness supported is 0.8 mm. 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Functional description</category></metadata></prolog><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><section id="GUID-3225DD38-160F-42B4-A279-10AA00359615" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">The construction</title><p class="- topic/p ">The Z motion system consists of 2 independent adjustment units. They are positioned between media position unit and the printhead guidance. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">With printhead guidance and drive. 
</p><fig id="GUID-18A77C2A-F6AC-4D7B-986B-40D97CA332EF" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-AC1CE0FC-2853-4522-B390-1266D9230722-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-AC1CE0FC-2853-4522-B390-1266D9230722-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">With MPU frame in place. 
</p><fig id="GUID-3C0860AE-1450-4D95-8682-6249420460DB" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-3CD05EF3-35E0-46A5-B285-40E876197146-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-3CD05EF3-35E0-46A5-B285-40E876197146-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">Due to the construction the guidance system stays completely parallel to the platen. 
</p></section><section id="SECTION_A471570BB53A435CA468AD4587BB93E4" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Components of the adjustment units</title><fig id="GUID-DBA5C253-D3D4-4AF0-AA2D-F2EAD9EC77AE" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-6D843929-0310-4B9B-BBD6-F7CA2457AFCA-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-6D843929-0310-4B9B-BBD6-F7CA2457AFCA-low.png"/></fig><table id="GUID-9C4FAD82-5078-472D-B680-06D134DE5073" pgwide="1" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="45*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="45*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Item 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Name 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Function 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Guidance bracket. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Bracket on which the printhead guidance is mounted. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Leaf springs. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The leaf springs hold the guidance bracket in parallel with the media positioning unit. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Z motion system Height Adjustment right motor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 03M3 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">ZMS_HA_RIGHT_MO</compsignal></comp> / <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Z motion system Height Adjustment left motor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 03M4 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">ZMS_HA_LEFT_MO</compsignal></comp>. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The adjustment motor (24V) moves the lever that lifts the guidance bracket. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Z motion system home right sensor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 03B6 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">ZMS_HOME_RIGHT_SE</compsignal></comp> / <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Z motion system home left sensor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 03B5 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">ZMS_HOME_LEFT_SE</compsignal></comp>. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The home sensors are used for the initialization of the home position . This is the highest position of the printhead guidance. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Lever. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The lever is the lifting mechanism connected to the guidance bracket. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Actuator bracket. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The actuator bracket is mounted on the lower frame and holds the actuator. 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-AED0C6E2-8104-4AD4-996F-29BDDA1DBE8D" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">The positions of the adjustment unit</title></section><section id="GUID-79CB18DB-5CCC-4B53-AA76-62FE9F42D392" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">The low position</title><fig id="GUID-56E88942-67A5-48E5-A5ED-858B291692C6" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-CD8C4101-D598-4C80-8339-AA2B444B696D-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-CD8C4101-D598-4C80-8339-AA2B444B696D-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">In the low position the printhead guidance is at the lowest position. At this position the printheads should not touch the platen. 
</p><note id="GUID-F5CD01D1-3732-4911-94C3-4553C2CAC1E7" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">When the motor is removed the matrix plate WILL touch the platen. That’s why the dis-assembly is only allowed with the carriage in the home position. 
</p></note><p class="- topic/p ">When lifting the Guidance bracket, the Spring-leafs bend upwards. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-1070FD93-CFAD-4011-8EAB-1BB9341AD686" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">The home position</title><fig id="GUID-96D02A21-77E5-4E1E-B8E0-4CDE7D1DED2C" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-33ACA798-FF23-44BC-93DF-467D8E2CE7E1-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-33ACA798-FF23-44BC-93DF-467D8E2CE7E1-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">The home position is the reference position for the height adjustment unit. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">When the printing system is switched ON / initialized the actuators on both sides will search for their home positions. They start to move the guidance brackets up. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The home position is reached when the lever is detected by the home sensors. At this moment the height adjustment unit is initialized and ready for regular operation. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Just before printing on a media the height adjustment unit moves to the correct height for the media used. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The height difference between the lowest position and the highest position is 5 mm. For this height the actuator has to move 38 mm. 
</p></section></conbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-6E558F02-B791-411E-A632-D506452606BD.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Functional description</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
